<HEADLINE> Philippine President Warns Poll Cheaters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos on
Saturday issued a strong warning against political parties
planning to rig the results of next Monday's national elections,
saying that "no fraud or cheating from any side will be
tolerated."
</P>
<P>
"The Ramos administration is pledged to insure honest, orderly
and peaceful elections (HOPE)," said Ramos in a pre-election
statement.
</P>
<P>
Ramos directed all agencies and their personnel who have been
deputized by the Commission on Elections (Comelec), especially the
Armed Forces and the National Police, "to be strictly correct and
fair in performing their election duties."
</P>
<P>
"As president, I myself will see to it that such HOPE, which we
all share, is fulfilled, and that no fraud or cheating from any
side will be tolerated," Ramos stressed.
</P>
<P>
As he warned the poll cheaters, Ramos exhorted the electorate
to exercise their sovereign right to elect their next group of
political leaders freely, democratically and intelligently.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the citizenry to be vigilant on the day of voting
and the counting of votes to make sure that the electoral process
will be free of fraud and highly acceptable to the citizenry.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, some 34 million registered Filipino voters will go
to the polls to vote a new president, as well as a new vice
president, 12 out of 24 senators, all 255 members of the House of
Representatives and thousands of local government officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
