<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Movie Whitewashing Japan's Aggression be Shown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 9 (Xinhua) -- A controversial Japanese film called
"Pride -- the Fatal Moment", which depicts Japan's aggression to
neighboring nations during World War Two as self-defending and
just, will be put on show later this month.
</P>
<P>
The film deals with the trial and last days of General Hideki
Tojo, Japan's wartime prime minister, who was executed as a war
criminal by the International Military Tribunal for the Far East
in November 1948.
</P>
<P>
Distorting historical facts, the movie portrays the
Asia-Pacific War Japan launched in early 1940s as the liberation
of Asian nations from the colonialism of European countries and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
It also depicts charges against Japanese troops of war crimes
as almost frame-ups with hearsay evidence and overstatement,
including the Nanjing Massacre in which about 300,000 people were
slaughtered by the Japanese army in the capital of China's Jiangsu
province in December 1937.
</P>
<P>
The movie reflects an opinion called the "historical view of
liberalism" which denies Japan's invasion of its neighbors on the
grounds that Japan would lose pride if it acknowledged the
aggression.
</P>
<P>
Isao Nakamura, president of Higashi-Nihon House Co. Ltd, the
main investor in the project, is a big supporter of the opinion.
</P>
<P>
The film, however, has come under attack from many Japanese
since previews were given last month.
</P>
<P>
A "Society to Criticize Pride -- the Fatal Movement", which was
set up on April 20, blasted the production, claiming that it
distorted history and betrayed the Japanese people's willingness
for peace.
</P>
<P>
"We can not keep silent over the movie as it has great
potential to influence to the public especially the young," the
society said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
China expressed outrage Saturday at the movie with Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao saying that making such a
film "is bound to be strongly condemned by people who face up to
history and love peace".
</P>
<P>
"Hideki Tojo was the chief criminal of the aggressive war. We
feel shocked and indignant over the fact that some people in Japan
produced such a movie to whitewash aggression and sing the praises
of Hideki Tojo." he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
