<HEADLINE> Paraguayan Campos of Beijing Guo'an Heads For World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Paraguayan international striker
Jorge Luis Campos of Beijing Guo'an became the first ever player
from the Chinese professional league to play the World Cup in
France this upcoming summer.
</P>
<P>
Campos has been selected in the 22-men Paraguay national squad
for the World Cup finals in June, which was announced on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Campos, last season's Player of the Year in China's first
division, would be the only player from the Chinese league in the
world primary soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
China did not qualify for the finals from the Asian zone.
</P>
<P>
Campos is a good message from the Chinese league and Guo'an to
the worldwide soccer, a club official said on Saturday after he
was informed of the news.
</P>
<P>
Yang Zuwu, vice manager of the club, said: "It (selection of
Campos) would help the world get to know the Chinese soccer, as
well as Guo'an."
</P>
<P>
"Chinese soccer had not been known by the world until dozens of
foreign players flowed in," said Yang on a telephone interview of
Xinhua. "China soccer gets more contact with the soccer world
following more international games, which results in the
improvement of our abroad introduced players."
</P>
<P>
The Paraguay Football Association (PFA) previously asked the
Chinese club to release Campos for a series of World Cup warm-up
matches, the Kirin Cup tournament in Tokyo through May 17-21 and
friendlies against the Netherlands, Romania and Belgium in June on
tour in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Yand said: "We had planned to keep Campos for league matches
against Vanguards Huandao on May 17 and Dalian Wanda on May 31,
but it is hard to get a nod from the PFA."
</P>
<P>
Campos is now in Chengdu, capital of the Sichuan Province,
preparing for match against Sichuan Quanxing on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He will fly to Japan to join the national team for the Kirin
Cup.
</P>
<P>
Campos, who came to Guo'an in the 1997-98 season from
Paraguayan domestic league, has extended his contract with the
club through this season.
</P>
<P>
"Campos is to play another full season for us," Yang said. "But
I'm not sure weather he will stay here after than."  
</P>
</TEXT>
