<HEADLINE> Presidents of Zimbabwe, Indonesia Arrive in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe and
Indonesian President Suharto arrived here on Saturday to attend
the eighth summit of the Group-15.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak discussed with Mugabe in the
afternoon the agenda of the three-day summit of 16 developing
countries due to open here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Suharto, who was greeted by Mubarak at the airport, will spend
another two days after the summit for an official visit to Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The G-15, founded in September, 1989, comprises Egypt, India,
Indonesia, Malaysia, Algeria, Zimbabwe, Senegal, Nigeria, Kenya,
Argentina, Jamaica, Venezuela, Mexico, Brazil, Peru and Chile.
</P>
<P>
The summit will focus on the Asian financial turmoil,
South-South cooperation and South-North dialog.
</P>
<P>
Seven heads of state, three vice presidents, two prime
ministers and several ministers are expected to take part in the
gathering. 
</P>
