<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Global Ad Industry Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Global advertising industry is
expected to grow six percent to 434 billion U.S. dollars this
year, U.S. industry data show.
</P>
<P>
The industry has averaged the six percent growth rate for the
last three years, according to U.S. newspaper Investor's Business
Daily on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Big ad agencies' revenue composition is changing with
traditional business in radio, TV and printing media shifting to
public relations, events, sports marketing and products promotion.
</P>
<P>
Major multinational ad agencies have embarked on consolidation
to expand business with current biggest players stationed in New
York and London while new subgroup leaders are emerging.
</P>
<P>
Despite its tiny portion of the industry, Internet advertising
sees a new, fast-growing perspective from a business of 600
million U.S. dollars in 1997 to about 5 billion dollars by 2000,
web-search firm Yahoo predicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
