leadership agree on this issue," he said.
</P>
<P>
It is important that the Washington talks between the
Palestinians and the Israelis will be held as scheduled on May 11
and "No party has the right to unilaterally reject attending the
talks," he added.
</P>
<P>
The talks will have no new topics, but stick to discussion of
what the U.S. raised before, said Nasri.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last month, the U.S. proposed for Israel to evacuate
from 13.1 percent of the occupied Palestinian land, but Israel
rejected it. The U.S. then mediated the meetings between both
sides in London, but still failed to persuade Israeli to accept
its proposal.
</P>
<P>
Washington meetings are widely thought as a continuation of
the U.S. efforts after London meetings to push forward the
Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiation which has been stalled for
more than a year due to Jewish settlement expansion in Arab East
Jerusalem. 
