<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan's Drug-Control Efforts Praised by U.N. Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Drug-control work by southwest
China's Yunnan Province was praised today by a high-ranking U.N.
official who had just completed his three-day visit to the region.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Yunnan governor Li Jiating, Pino Arlacchi, deputy
secretary-general and executive director of the United Nations'
Drug Control Program, said he was deeply impressed by Yunnan's
achievements in drug-control and rehabilitation of addicts.
</P>
<P>
Located near the "Golden Triangle" area which is one of the
three main sources for the drug trade, Yunnan Province has issued
more than 10 drug-control codes and regulations in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has 147 special drug-enforcement groups with nearly
2,000 officers. Each year about 80 percent of China's drug cases
occur in Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
More than 80 rehabilitation centers have been established in
the province, treating more than 20,000 addicts each year.
</P>
</TEXT>
