<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Wants to be Vital Part of Asia-Europe Channel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Romania Senate Chairman Petre
Roman proposed that Romania must begin its infrastructure
preparations to make sure that it can be part of the
transportation and energy channel connecting Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Roman made the remarks on Saturday night when he was just back
from Turkey after attending the Parliamentary forum of the
organization of economic cooperation in the Black Sea region.
</P>
<P>
Romania must keep a long-range foresight on the construction
of the channel to make sure that Romania can play a vital role in
it, The Romania News Agency on Sunday quoted Roman as saying.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the modernized passageway for transportation
and energy is a project connecting the mid-Asian countries and the
Black Sea area.
</P>
<P>
Although the project is still in planning stage, all related
nations have already begun competing each other trying to be a
part of the future passageway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
