<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Second Clay Title of 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis revenged her defeat six
weeks ago by beating Venus Williams 6-3, 2-6, 6-3 on Sunday to win
the 926,250 U.S. dollars Italian Open.
</P>
<P>
By winning her fourth title of the year, also her second clay
title, Hingis improved to 5-2 against Williams who beat Hingis in
the semi-final at Key Biscayne, Florida in March and in their
first match of the year in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Hingis dropped her serve twice in the second after
winning the first set, and began the third set with a break but
had to fight to emerge victorious after four more breaks of serve
before the end.
</P>
<P>
The match lasted nearly two hours.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, winner of three of last year's four Grand Slams, has
now triumphed at the Australian Open, Indian Wells, Hamburg and
Rome so far this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
