<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Wins Spanish Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, May 10 (Xinhua) -- World championship leader Mika
Hakkinen won the Spanish Grand Prix in his McLaren-Mercedes in
Barcelona on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In his third victory of the year, Hakkinen finished ahead of
his Scottish teammate David Coulthard as McLarens again finished
1-2.
</P>
<P>
Two-time world champion Michael Schumacher of Germany was third
in his Ferrari.
</P>
<P>
Hakkinen, who won the opening two races of the season in
Australia and Brazil, increased his lead after five championship
races to seven points over Coulthard.
</P>
<P>
The Finn now has 36 points to Coulthard's 29 and Schumacher's
24. He clocked 1 hour 33 minutes 37.621 seconds to complete the 65
laps of the 4.728km circuit, a total of 307.320km.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Wurz of Austria was fourth in his Benetton, followed
by Brazilian Rubens Barrichello in a Stewart-Ford and defending
world champion Jacques Villeneuve of Canada in a Williams.
</P>
</TEXT>
