<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Official Speaks Highly Of Yunnan's Drug Rehabilitation Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan Province
today was praised by a high-ranking U.N. official for its drug
rehabilitation and control program.
</P>
<P>
After visiting the rehabilitation center in Kunming, capital of
Yunnan, Pino Arlacchi, deputy secretary-general and executive
director of the United Nations Drug Control Program, said that he
"was deeply moved."
</P>
<P>
Arlacchi said that he has seen a very efficient and very
careful way to treat addiction with rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that it is a good investment to channel
resources here in this country and in this region, and I will do
my best to let the international community know that Yunnan is a
model for China and for the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1989, the Kunming Rehabilitation Center is the
largest in east and south Asia. It receives more than 5,000 drug
addicts every year.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Yuzu, head of the center, it has
successfully developed a medicine to help addicts give up their
habit.
</P>
<P>
He said that for people coming there for rehabilitation, the
center is like a family and a hospital.
</P>
<P>
"We administrate them strictly but treat and cure them
warmheartedly," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, the cure rate of the center for the jobless
is 15 percent, and the figure for those who have families is over
60 percent, both exceeding the world average. 
</P>
</TEXT>
