<HEADLINE> Production of Railway Vehicles Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Production of railway vehicles went
down in February, 1998, according to the latest figures from the
State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
China manufactured locomotives with a total capacity of 180,000
kW, down 0.7 percent from the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country produced 42 railway passenger coaches
and internal combustion engines with a combined capacity of 9.22
million KW, down 77.7 percent, and 17.4 percent, respectively.
</P>
