<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thousands of Visitors Gather in Haining for Tide-watching </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 50,000 people gathered
today in the ancient city of Haining in east China's Zhejiang
Province to attend tide-watching activities.
</P>
<P>
The tide of the Qiantang River near Haining is one of the most
amazing phenomena in China. Scientists say that the bell-shaped
mouth of the Qiantang River near the city helps form the
not-to-be-missed "Haining Tide," whose crest can be as high as 3.5
meters.
</P>
<P>
Traditionally, only every mid-August of the traditional Chinese
calendar was considered as a golden season for tide-watching in
Haining, but scientists say that the spring tide there is also
splendid.
</P>
<P>
"Actually, the Haining Tide can be seen 120 days of the year;
every month there will be nearly 20,000 visitors watching the
tide," said an official with the local tourist department.
</P>
<P>
Besides the tide-watching activities being held through
Wednesday, many other sightseeing activities, folk arts and trade
fairs have also been organized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
