<HEADLINE> Driver Killed in Wuhan Car Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 10 (Xinhua) -- A driver died in a car explosion at
11:50 this morning in Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to witnesses, a black car exploded at the junction of
the Fourth Qianjin Road and Zizhi Street. The driver, the sole
occupant of the car, died on the spot. The explosion also set fire
to a red taxi in front of the car, and the windows of two shops
nearby were cracked.
</P>
<P>
The black car belongs to a bank branch in the Wuchang District
of the city, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Kangyan, director of the the city's Bureau of Public
Security, said the explosion is a criminal case and is under
investigation.
</P>
<P>
On Feb. 24, a bus explosion in the city caused by two peasants
claimed 16 lives.  
</P>
