<HEADLINE> 23 Pilgrims Killed in Bus Accident in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three pilgrims were killed
and more than 20 others injured when a bus from Kedarnath shrine
plunged into a deep river in Uttar pradesh of northern India
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that authorities were finding it
difficult to reach the accident site following road blockade
caused by uprooted trees and disruption of telecommunication
services due to incessant rains in the region in the past few
days.
</P>
<P>
This is the second major mishap in the Chamoli district in the
past three days. On Friday last, 29 people were killed and 16
others injured when a private bus fell into Alaknanda river.
