<HEADLINE> Suzhou Industrial Park Builds Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the largest
infrastructure project in the Sino-Singaporean Suzhou Industrial
Park, the Huaneng Power Plant, has begun in Taichang City.
</P>
<P>
The power plant, which will be used by the park, has an
installation capacity of three million kilowatts (kw). Its first
phase includes two 300,000 kw power generators, which will begin
generating power in 1999 and 2000.
</P>
<P>
The industrial park puts a high priority on the construction of
infrastructure facilities. Currently, it has a water works, a gas
plant, a sewage plant and a heat-supply plant. The zone's
investment in infrastructure is 4.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The plants have been designed primarily for the industrial park
and will serve other clients in Suzhou only when the park has
ample supplies, according to an official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
