<HEADLINE> Tibet's New People's Congress Session Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 10 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Seventh
Tibet Autonomous Regional People's Congress opened today in
Lhasa. Gyaincain Norbu, chairman of the autonomous region,
reported on the government's work.
</P>
<P>
The Gross Domestic Product (GDP) of Tibet increased by 13.2
percent annually over the past five years, 7.4 percentage points
higher than the annual growth rate in the previous five years,
according to Gyaincain's report.
</P>
<P>
He said that the accumulated fixed assets investment in the
last five years hit 14.1 billion yuan (1.7 billion U.S. dollars),
3.2 times that of the previous five years.
</P>
<P>
The import and export trade volume in this five-year period was
709 million U.S. dollars, 2.7 times that of the previous five
years, he added.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized in his report that the GDP of Tibet will double
that of 2000 when the autonomous region celebrates the 50th
anniversary of its founding in 2015.  
</P>
