<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are business briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
SANAA -- Yemeni Undersecretary of Petroleum and Mineral Wealth
Ministry Rasheed Barbaa said Saturday that there were positive
indications about the existence of gold mines in several Yemeni
governorates.
</P>
<P>
He said that exploration for gold has been under way in the
governorates of Hadramout, Haja and Zamar.
</P>
<P>
He also expected that zinc and lead would be found in the Naham
region of Sanaa governorate.
</P>
<P>
Gold search in Yemen actually began in the early 1980s, but
gold found then was in small quantities and not good enough for
export.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- China is to open a silk factory in the industrial free
zone of Ismailia, Egypt, with an investment of about 2.4 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ismailia governor said Chinese side will provide technology and
equipment, while Egyptian side provide premises and necessary
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Electricity has been restored in the sandstorm-hit
Basra, Nasseriya and Emara governorates in southern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency reported that the sandstorms which swept
southern Iraq last week destroyed the 400-kilovolt electricity
line and 21 42-meter-high pylons.
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Head of the European Commission Office in Amman Yves
Gazo said here Sunday that EU's aid to the countries in the Middle
East region accounted for 54 percent of its total assistance of
1.68 billion ecu (about 1.81 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said the EU will continue its economic support for the
region.
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordan's National carrier Royal Jordanian (RJ) is to
sell five aged TriStar aircraft and lease two Airbuses of A-310
and A-320 as part of its efforts to modernize its fleet and boost
its global network.
</P>
<P>
The move, which will be completed in a year, can save the
airlines 27 million to 30 million dollars annually due to the
per-hour flying cost difference between the two types of aircraft,
semi-official Jordan Times quoted RJ's President Nader Dahabi as
saying Sunday.


10/05/98 14:50 GMT

NNNN
22:58 22:59 g # PAB
</P>
