<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 10 (Xinhua) -- The index of the Kuwait Stock
Exchange dropped by 13.2 points to close at 2,321.9 points on
Sunday, the second consecutive day in a new trading week starting
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was 2,335.1 points on Saturday, a drop of 2.9 points from
the closing of last trading week ended on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A report issued by the stock exchange said the three variables,
namely volume, value and transactions, dropped on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The volume dropped to 76.57 million shares from 179.925
million, the dealings decreased to 2,108 from 4,051 and the
turnover came down to 19.99 million Kuwait dinars (65.96 million
U.S. dollars) from 47.689 million dinars (157.36 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The sectors of bank, investment, insurance, real estate,
industries, services, food and investment funds all witnessed a
downtrend in the day.
</P>
<P>
The index drop is in sharp contrast with the bullish market
during the last two consecutive trading weeks ending last
Wednesday, spurred by the strong confidence in the plans of the
new government to boost the economy.
</P>
<P>
A total of 78 listed companies and mutual funds are trading
shares in the Kuwait Stock Exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
