<DOCNO> XIE19980510.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Wanda Keeps Lead in Chinese Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Leaders Dalian Wanda scored a 3-0
home win over Vanguards Huandao on Sunday to sit atop after 10
rounds in the Chinese soccer first division league.
</P>
<P>
With only three minutes into the game, Hao Haidong, the best
Chinese scorer, swung in his header off a right-wing pass from Li
Ming who failed to convert from the penalty spot 35 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the 69th minute, substitute Wang Tao put Wanda 2-0 as goalie
Fu Bin failed to block his header from entering the net.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes later, Li Ming eventually scored his goal in a
melee off a corner kick to help Wanda pocket 25 points from 10
rounds of matches.
</P>
<P>
Against the Vanguards, the Wanda eleven had missed several
great chances as their three kicks bounced off either from the bar
or from the post while Vanguards failed to launch serious attacks
throughout the game.
</P>
<P>
In the other games, both Beijing Guo'an and Shanghai Shenhua
failed to garner three points from their away games to remain at
the second and third spots respectively in the league.
</P>
<P>
Guo'an lost its two great chances in the second half as Jorge
Luis Campos Velazquz of Paraguay fired his kick against the right
post and his teammate slammed the ball inches over the bar minutes
later for a scoreless tie against Sichuan Quanxing.
</P>
<P>
Against rainy weather, Shenhua tied 2-2 against Guangzhou
Apollo for one point from the away game, failing to overtake
Guo'an for the second spot as it still lagged behind one point.
</P>
<P>
Simicic Ioica of Yugoslavia netted in two goals, the first and
the last, to help Apollo stop its losing streak in the league.
</P>
<P>
In other games of the day, Shandong Luneng savored its home win
of 3-1 against Yanbian Aodong, Shenyang Haishi beat visiting
Chinese Army 2-1, Wuhai Yaqi lost its home game 2-1 to Shenzhen
Pi'an while Qingdao Hainiu tied scoreless with Guangzhou Songri.
</P>
