<HEADLINE> Iraqi FM Briefs Jordanian Official on Iraqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Iraqi Foreign Minister
Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf Sunday briefed Jordan's acting foreign
minister on Iraq's cooperation with the United Nations on arms
inspection.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Jordan's Talal Sat'an Al Hassan, al-Sahhaf
presented the file of Iraqi cooperation with the U.N. Security
Council and the U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of
dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, in carrying out
relevant resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The briefing also covered the efforts made by the Security
Council to close the weapons file about Iraq and shift from the
point of disarmament of Iraq to that of permanent monitoring of
Iraqi military capabilities.
</P>
<P>
"The briefing was evidenced by all the relevant documents that
certify Iraqi cooperation with the Security Council and the
UNSCOM," said al-Sahhaf in a statement to Jordan's official news
agency.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sahhaf arrived here late Saturday night on a three-day
official visit to enlist Jordan's help for lifting the sanctions
imposed on Iraq since its invasion of Kuwait in 1990. He is
expected to deliver King Hussein a message from Iraqi President
Saddam Hussein later during his visit.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the Security Council decided to renew the
sanctions on Iraq. The sanctions can only be lifted after the
Security Council certifies that Iraq has eliminated all its
weapons of mass destruction. 
</P>
