</P>
<P>
During the two-day summit beginning Sunday, leaders of the ten
member countries of the ECO will review economic cooperation
strategy for the region with trade transport, communication and
energy on the priority list, the report said.
</P>
<P>
"Besides economic issues, the relentless fighting in
Afghanistan is likely to figure in the conference where civil war
is being considered as a major obstacle in the economic activities
in the region," the report quoted diplomatic sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ECO is the successor of the Regional Cooperation for
Development which was founded by Pakistan, Iran and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the organization was expanded to include seven new
members which are Afghanistan, Azerbaijan, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan,
Tajikistan, Turkmenistan and Uzbekistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
