<HEADLINE> hke051030 -5 Philippine Presidential Bets Pledge Honest Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 10 (Xinhua) -- On the eve of Monday's elections,
five presidential candidates and three vice presidential bets
signed here Sunday a covenant to reaffirm their commitment to
ensure the holding of honest and peaceful elections.
</P>
<P>
The three-page document was signed by the candidates at the
Presidential Palace during a breakfast meeting hosted by President
Fidel Ramos to get their support for credible elections.
</P>
<P>
Only five of the 10 presidential bets and four of the nine vice
presidential aspirants attended the meeting although Ramos invited
all the candidates.
</P>
<P>
The presidential bets who signed the covenant were House
Speaker Jose de Venecia of the ruling Lakas-NUCD party, Vice
President Joseph Estrada of the Laban ng Makabayang Masang
Pilipino (Fight of Patriotic Filipinos Masses), former Defense
Secretary Renato de Villa of the Democratic Reform Coalition
Party, former Manila Mayor Alfredo Lim of the Liberal Party and
Senator Raul Roco of the Aksyon Demokratiko (Democratic Action).
</P>
<P>
Only three vice presidential candidates responded to the call
by the President. They were Estrada's partner Senator Edgardo
Angara, Roco's running mate Irene Santiago and Senator Francisco
Tatad of the People's Reform Party.
</P>
<P>
President Ramos, Senate President Neptali Gonzales, Chairman
Bernardo Pardo and five commissioners of the Commission on
Elections, heads of two citizens' monitoring groups and leaders of
religious groups also inked the document as witnesses.
</P>
<P>
In the covenant, the candidates cast aside violence and all
forms of cheating, intimidation or similar acts during the
elections and especially on the election day.
</P>
<P>
In his opening remarks, Ramos said a truly qualified aspirant
does not have "to resort to violence and fraud just to win." All
it takes is to reach out to the masses and prove that he or she
has the best program of government, he added. 
</P>
