<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, May 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Some components destined for the Bushehr nuclear
power plant, along with the vehicle transporting them, have been
stolen in Isfahan, central Iran, the morning newspaper Iran Daily
reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
An informed source told the daily on Saturday from southern
coastal province of Bushehr that the spare parts had previously
been at Isfahan Shahrif University of Technology for testing. But
he did not specify the identities of the stolen components and the
time when they were stolen. (Iran-Nuclear Plant-Stealth)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. police in riot gear used tear gas to
disperse anti-Klan demonstrators, who broke through a fence and
rained bottles and rocks to disrupt a Ku Klux Klan rally in
Michigan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of demonstrators showed up, many flashing signs
reading "Smash the Klan" in their action against the Klan rally at
Ann Arbor, Michigan. At least five people were treated for minor
injuries, but no arrests were made, the Associated Press
reported. (US-Demonstration)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic said here
Saturday that the referendum result in Serbia last month
demonstrated that it is impossible for the country to accept any
foreign meddling in the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with U.S. presidential envoys Richard Holbrooke
and Robert Gelbard, Milosevic said that Yugoslavia hopes to
develop bilateral ties and cooperation with the United States on
the basis of equality, mutual respect and non-interference in each
other's internal affairs, the Tanjug news agency
reported. (Yugoslavia-US-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Some 20,000 Cambodian refugees, mostly Khmer Rouge
dependents, are being evacuated to a new camp in the northern Thai
province of Si Sa Ket for better control and security reasons, the
Bangkok Post reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said Thai military officials had begun relocating
those refugees from a makeshift camp about eight kilometers from
the border to a nearby camp. The evacuation of the refugees, who
fled the recent fighting in Cambodia between government forces and
the Khmer Rouge guerrillas, is expected to be completed in seven
days, said province governor Poj Jaiman, who inspected the
evacuation Saturday. (Thailand-Cambodia-Refugees) 
</P>
