<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Makes Important Speech on Criterion for Truth (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
made an important speech at a forum marking the 20th anniversary
of a nationwide debate on the criterion for verifying truth here
on May 8.
</P>
<P>
Following is an excerpt of the speech by Hu, who is also a
member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee:
</P>
<P>
Twenty years ago, our Party and country held a major debate on
whether practice is the sole criterion for verifying
truth. Initiating a nationwide mind-emancipation drive guided by
Marxism, the debate made ideological preparations for the
epoch-making Third Plenary Session of the 11th CPC Central
Committee, and exerted a significant and far-reaching influence
over the historical process of the Party and the country.
</P>
<P>
Remembering the debate today is of great importance for holding
high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, further
emancipating the mind, using and developing Deng Xiaoping Theory
creatively, solving all kinds of problems, and propelling the
great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The debate on the criterion for verifying truth took place when
our Party and country were facing a major historical transition,
and was carried out under the leadership and with the support of
the older generation of proletarian revolutionaries such as Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In May 1978 a publication run by the CPC Central Committee
Party School for internal circulation first carried the article
titled ``Practice is the Sole Criterion for Verifying Truth'',
which had been pre-checked by Hu Yaobang. On the following day,
the article was published in the Guangming Daily, and was then
transmitted by Xinhua News Agency around the country. Thus there
started a major debate on the criterion for seeking truth.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980510.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-10 </DATE_TIME>
