<DOCNO> XIE19980510.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Makes Important Speech on Criterion of Truth (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is proper to say that the debate was an ideological
forerunner for the great transition, with deep and far-reaching
significance in our Party's history since the founding of the
People's Republic achieved at the Third Plenary Session of the
11th CPC Central Commission, as well as for the reform and
opening-up over the next two decades. It laid a theoretical
foundation for our Party to re-establish Marxist ideological,
political and organizational lines.
</P>
<P>
In his speech titled ``Emancipate the Mind, Seek Truth from
Practice, Unite and Adopt a Forward-Looking Attitude'', made at
the Central Work Conference on December 13, 1978, Deng Xiaoping
spoke highly of the great significance of the debate, saying, "The
current debate on whether practice is the sole criterion for
verifying truth is, in fact, also one on whether to emancipate our
minds.
</P>
<P>
"A party, a country, or a nation, if it adopts a dogmatic
attitude, will fail to make any progress, thus losing its vitality
and ultimately ceasing to exist.
</P>
<P>
"Our socialist modernization can be carried out smoothly, and
the theories of Marxism and Mao Zedong Thought will develop
smoothly, only if we emancipate our minds, seek truth from facts,
proceed from reality and combine theory with reality.
</P>
<P>
"In this sense, the debate on the criterion for truth is indeed
an issue concerning ideological and political lines, and the
future and destiny of the Party and the country."
</P>
</TEXT>
