<HEADLINE> Gunmen Raid Airline's Offices in Nairobi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Gunmen robbed Emirate Airlines'
offices in Nairobi Saturday in a new wave of crimes hitting the
Kenyan capital where a tycoon kidnapped at a ransom of about
830,000 US Dollars was rescued by police only a few days ago.
</P>
<P>
The six robbers, armed with pistols, robbed guests and stole
cash at the offices at 11:00 a.m. on the 20th floor of View Park
Towers downtown, before snatching a Toyota Corolla from a woman
outside, local press reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A guard was shot in the right shoulder when he attempted to
trap the fleeing gunmen by locking the main door of the ground
floor.
</P>
<P>
"I was closing the exit to stop three of the robbers when one
drew a gun and shot. He aimed at my head but I dodged and the
bullet caught my right shoulder," said Vincent Odima, the guard.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of office clerks, foreigners and local clients buying
tickets were ordered to lie down and relieved of cash and
personal effects during the 20-minute raid.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen stole 64,885 Kenyan Shillings (about 1,080 US
Dollars) and 2,190 U.S. Dollars from the office and an unknown
amount of money from the travellers.
</P>
<P>
They had disguised themselves by wearing Moslem caps.
</P>
<P>
Police said the gangsters were being pursued. 
</P>
</TEXT>
