<HEADLINE> Ramos Calls for Honest, Orderly, Peaceful Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Outgoing Philippine President Fidel
Ramos Sunday called for "clean, credible, orderly and peaceful"
elections on May 11.
</P>
<P>
"On the part of the government, we will do everything possible
to make sure that the elections will be clean, credible, orderly
and peaceful, and that the real will of the people shall prevail,"
he said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the citizenry to be vigilant on the days of
voting and counting to ensure the electoral process is free of
fraud and highly acceptable to the general public.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he issued a strong warning against political parties
planning to rig the results of the May 11 elections, stressing
that "no fraud or cheating from any side will be tolerated."
</P>
<P>
"The Ramos administration is pledged to ensure honest, orderly
and peaceful elections. As a president, I myself will see to it
that such elections which we all share is fulfilled, and that no
fraud and cheating from any side will be tolerated," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos has directed all agencies and their personnel, especially
the armed forces and the national police, "to be strictly correct
and fair in performing their election duties."
</P>
<P>
About 116,000 government troops and policemen have been
deployed around the country. The Commission on Elections also puts
33 hot spots under its direct control.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, Ramos also reiterated his call on the 34
million voters to exercise their sovereign right to elect their
next group of political leaders "freely, democratically and
intelligently."
</P>
<P>
"Each of us must do his or her part -- to ensure that the
elections are conducted in a way that will manifest our democratic
and constitutional system," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the quality of the polls would reflect the
stability of the country's political system and its commitment to
the rule of law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
