<HEADLINE> Components of Iranian Nuclear Plant Stolen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Some components destined for the
Bushehr nuclear power plant, along with the vehicle transporting
them, have been stolen in Isfahan, central Iran, the morning
newspaper Iran Daily reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
An informed source told the daily on Saturday from southern
coastal province of Bushehr that the spare parts had previously
been at Isfahan Shahrif University of Technology for testing.
</P>
<P>
He did not specify the identities of the stolen components and
when they were stolen. It is believed the vehicle transporting the
components was the target of the thieves "because the missing
parts are not considered very important," he added.
</P>
<P>
The security forces are investigating the case, he said,
giving no more details.
</P>
<P>
The Bushehr 1,000-megawatt nuclear power plant is under
construction with the assistance of Russia under a contract of 1
billion U.S. dollars signed in January, 1995. 
</P>
