<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champions the Czech Republic
and Sweden reached the world ice hockey championship semifinals in
Basle on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs beat hosts Switzerland 3-1 and Sweden nipped
Belarus 2-1. Russia kept their hopes alive with a 6-1 win over
Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
The win left the Czechs with a perfect 2-0 record their
round-robin group. Their three rivals have all lost once so they
can do no worse than qualify second. Sweden were in a similar
position in their group.
</P>
<P>
Canada looked to have take a semifinal berth as well, but a
last minute goal by Finland forced a 3-3 draw and put Canada's
hopes on hold. If Canada lose to Sweden their fate could be
decided on goal difference. 
</P>
