<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures (3): Philippines' President &AMP; Vice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 10 (Xinhua) -- The president and vice-president of
the Philippines
</P>
<P>
The president is head of state, chief executive of the republic
and commander-in-chief of the armed forces. The president is
elected for a six-year term, and is not eligible for re-election.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president can serve two successive six-year terms.
</P>
<P>
Candidates for both posts are elected by direct universal
suffrage. They must be natural-born citizens, literate, at least
40 years of age, registered voters and residents in the
Philippines for at least 10 years prior to election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
