<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Province Set to Develop Three Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, May 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province's
deputy governor, Wu Changqing, said during a recent commodities
fair here that his province will lay emphasis on the development
of three areas between now and the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Development will center on areas along the Zhejiang-Jiangxi
Railway, as well as the economic belt along the Yangtze River and
Poyang Lake, and along the Beijing-Kowloon Railway.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi, located in the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze
River, is the hub of three economic development zones -- the Pearl
River Delta, Yangtze River Delta, and southeastern delta area in
Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi province has abundant mineral and agriculture
resources. The provincial government had approved 4,366
foreign-funded enterprises by the end of 1997, with total
investments standing at 3.69 billion US dollars. The province had
approved 850 Taiwan-funded enterprises by the end of March this
year, with total investments of 1.5 billion US dollars allocated
to some 80-odd project areas.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the provincial government has engaged in extensive
efforts to improve infrastructure facilities. All counties and
townships are currently linked by program-controlled telephones,
with the province's total installed generating capacity standing
at 5.02 million kw. The new Beijing-Kowloon railway has greatly
improved Jiangxi's transportation network.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has also introduced regulations to
improve the local investment environment and protect the rights of
investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980510.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diving Grand Prix Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
