<HEADLINE> Shanghai Street Tour Available on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Dropping in on the Web site
www.shanghaicommerce.com on the Internet can provide a panoramic
view of Shanghai's renowned Nanjing Boulevard, as famous in its
own way as Oxford Street in London and Broadway in New York City.
</P>
<P>
As one of 10 projects aimed at building Shanghai into an
information center, the Web site recently passed appraisal by
experts.
</P>
<P>
Now, approximately 180 shopping malls, collection shops and
brand-name stores with 100 years of history in the most bustling
downtown area in Shanghai, built in 1815, have a presence on the
Web.
</P>
<P>
A "surfer" at an Internet bar in the municipality's
Jinlingdonglu Street said: "Window shopping on the Web is easy and
interesting, and I can obtain up-to-date commercial information as
well."
</P>
<P>
Indeed, apart from its role as a guide for tourists and
shoppers, the system will also provide the latest commercial news,
prices and trade quotations as well as commodity surveys.
</P>
</TEXT>
