<HEADLINE> RC Lens clinch French League Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Defender Yohan Lachor scored the
crucial equalizer as RC Lens drew 1-1 at AJ Auxerre to win the
French soccer league championship for the first time on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They took their title on goal difference from Metz, who beat
Olympique Lyon 1-0 at home with a third minute goal by Bruno
Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
Auxerre went ahead after 13 minutes through midfielder Sabri
Lamouchi but Lachor secured Lens' vital point with his 53rd minute
equalizer. 
