<HEADLINE> Ramos Hosts Breakfast Meeting to Ensure Honest Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 10 (Xinhua) -- Outgoing Philippine President Fidel
Ramos hosted a breakfast meeting Sunday with candidates running
for president and vice president, the Presidential New Desk said.
</P>
<P>
The breakfast meeting began at 7:30 a.m. as scheduled and the
holding of "honest, orderly and peaceful" polls is the primary
concern of the meeting, it said.
</P>
<P>
As of late Saturday, six presidential candidates had accepted
the president's invitation and confirmed their participation.
</P>
<P>
The other guests invited are key government officials,
religious groups and heads of citizen monitoring groups.
</P>
<P>
During the breakfast, chiefs of the Commission on Elections,
the Philippine National Police, the Armed Forces of the
Philippines and other departments concerned were to introduce the
status of preparation for the elections.
</P>
<P>
Fraud, cheating and violence are feared in the elections. It
was reported that at least 33 people have died in election-related
violence.
</P>
<P>
The presidential bets attending the meeting were House Speaker
Jose de Venecia of the ruling Lakas-NUCD party, Vice President
Joseph Estrada of the Laban ng Makabayang Masang Pilipino (Fight
of Patriotic Filipino Masses), former Manila mayor Alfredo Lim of
the Liberal Party, former Defense Secretary Renato de Villa of the
Democratic Reform Coalition Party, Emilio Osmena of the
Progressive Movement for Devolution of Initiative Party and Manuel
Morato of the Partido Bansang Marangal (Decent Nation Party).
</P>
<P>
Former First Lady Imelda Marcos Saturday officially withdrew
from the contest, deciding to support Estrada who led with a 33
percent popularity rating in a latest survey. De Venecia followed
with 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
After Imelda's quit, 10 candidates are running for the
presidency in Monday's polls. Also at stake are the vice
presidency, 12 out of 24 senators, 250 House representatives, 78
provincial governors and some 1600 local mayors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
