<HEADLINE> Zuelle Wins Fourth Stage in Tour of Romandie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 9 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland's Alex Zuelle won the
fourth stage time trial of the Tour of Romandie cycling on
Saturday ahead of teammate and overall leader Laurent Dufaux.
</P>
<P>
Zuelle, 1996 world champion, completed the 18km distance in 23
minutes 34 seconds, 11 seconds clear of Dufaux and 15 in front of
Roland Meier, as Swiss riders swept the top four places.
</P>
<P>
Dufaux will carry a comfortable 1:17 margin over Zuelle in the
overall classification into Sunday's final stage, a 168km run from
Lausanne into Geneva.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the two-part stage, Italy's Paolo Bettini
snatched his first professional victory by beating compatriot
Fabio Baldato and Frenchman Francois Simon at the finish of a
100km run from Sion to Lausanne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
