<HEADLINE> New Railway Line to Be Built in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 10 (Xinhua) -- China will start from next month
the construction of a railway line linking Neijiang, in southwest
China's Sichuan Province, with this capital of Yunnan Province
next month.
</P>
<P>
The rail route is one of nine new ones to be built in China
this year, an official from the project headquarters announced
here today. It will cost an estimated 11.6 billion yuan (1.4
billion US dollars) and be completed in four years' time.
</P>
<P>
From Neijiang it will run through several cities in Sichuan,
Guizhou and Yunnan provinces before ending at Kunming, with a total
length of 854 km.
</P>
<P>
The line will be part of the north-south railway trunk in
China. Its operation will alleviate the transportation tension in
southwest China and speed up tourism and natural resources
development in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
