<HEADLINE> New Overseas-Funded Firm in Liaoning Begins Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 10 (Xinhua) -- The Great Wall Food (Dalian)
Co. Ltd, a joint venture between Taiwan and Japan, has started
operation in Wafangdian City, in northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest overseas-funded livestock products
processing firm ever built in Liaoning, according to a provincial
trade official.
</P>
<P>
The Great Wall Enterprise Co. Ltd, one of the partners, is the
second-largest food processing company in Taiwan, with a history
of 40 years. It has already opened five subsidiaries in Liaoning,
with a total investment of 50 million US dollars. The Marubeni
Co. Ltd, the other partner, is one of the five top commercial
firms in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The new company, built at a cost of 30 million US dollars,
engages in fodder production and chicken processing. It will add
processing of pork and beef and produce finished food in the near
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
